About
The Green Planet is the region’s first bio-dome that recreates the enchanting world of a tropical forest with its rich biodiversity of over 3,000 plants and animals. The enclosed ecosystem, located at CITY WALK, offers visitors an immersive expedition into the tropics. The unique venue has 4 levels of interaction for visitor with fascinating animal and plant species to see from Sloths, Tucan's and Tree porcupines to South American plants, vines, reptiles, fish and insects. A great destination for families and guests of all ages.
Duration: 2-3 hours
Meets animal welfare guidelines

4 contributions
A reasonable value couple of hours.
Oct 2024 • Family
As with all attractions in Dubai, the Green Planet is not cheap but it is worth a visit. We booked the sloth experience and Mark was a brilliant guide.

It is obvious that all the animals are not in their native environments but the Green Planet does a great job attempting to replicate them. And it is a novel touch for so many creatures to be side by side. Make sure you visit the basement, here we found Enock who was also very knowledgeable. The owl was one of our favourite creatures here.

The site is under expansion so it is a bit odd to see construction cranes outside the window but on the whole this is a good way to pass the time. I would say you don't need to allow more than two hours to see everything comfortably, even with young children.

Taxis are the most sensible way to get there - Burj Khalifa/Dubai Mall metro station is a good twenty minute walk, not all that pleasant in the heat and with the traffic.
Written November 3, 2024
